General:
  - TAB is equal to 4 spaces
  - blank line separates code blocks


Code arrangement:
  - assignment operator (=) column aligned to the nearest TAB
  - "{" and "}" operators are placed on new lines
  - (when reasonable) align symbol names to the nearest TAB
  - multiple boolean operations (usually inside "if" statements) should be aligned to eachother on new lines
  - (when reasonable) align function parameter container "()" to start from the nearest TAB, aligned with revious functions

Module naming:
  - CDD - complex device driver - non-standard device configuration